// bisect: asymmetric timeout (interp exceeded 8x budget; JIT produced a value — verify the node-walk terminates and agrees before reading this as a JIT bug)
// interp: Timeout
// jit:    Trace(Trace { epochs: [Epoch { events: [(0, I64(7))], capped: false }] })
// mutant: {let rec f = |n: i64| -> i64 select select n {i64:0 => str::len("abc"), _ => f(n - i64:1) + array::len([n])} {m if m <= i64:0 => i64:1 % m, m => f(m - i64:1)}; let v = f(i64:1); array::fold([i64:5, i64:7], v, |a, x| x)}
// minimized:

{
	let rec f = |n: i64| -> i64
		select
			select n {
				i64:0 => str::len("abc"),
				_ => f(n - i64:1)
			}
		{
			m if m <= i64:0 => i64:1 % m,
			m => f(m - i64:1)
	    };
	let v = f(i64:1);
	array::fold([i64:5, i64:7], v, |a, x| x)
}

// RULED + FIXED (Eric, 2026-07-23): depth-limit-exceeded is a
// SETTLED, DELIVERED tainted bottom (node/lambda.rs trip site) — an
// identical retry re-trips deterministically, so re-evaluation waits
// for a genuine input event. Delivery matches the kernel's
// abort-to-placeholder seam AND breaks the tail-loop wedge (retained
// tail arms re-fired off their own formal deliveries under absence,
// spinning one never-ending cycle). Both modes now AGREE: Trace([7]),
// idle. Original triage below.
// TRIAGE (claude, 2026-07-23): the accepted abort-vs-retry seam, pending
// Eric's ruling per the asymmetric-timeout policy. f(1) <-> f(2) is
// INFINITELY mutually recursive through the nested selects. Interp:
// depth-trip -> transient-recursion retry EVERY cycle, never idle, no
// value ever (the fold's init arrives as ABSENCE, blocking the node).
// JIT: aborts once to a tainted placeholder; the acc-ignoring fold
// callback recovers by the consumption rule and emits 7, then idles.
// Control: a plain bottom init (1/0) AGREEs in both modes — the split
// is delivery mode (tainted TagValue vs absence), not recovery logic.
// Under the worked-cycle deadline (3b0bc013) this class records as a
// deterministic cap-mismatch (interp [] capped vs jit [7] idle) — and
// it is WHY cap-mismatch must stay a recorded divergence: prefix-pass
// cannot distinguish "interp merely slow" (fib) from "JIT value the
// interp never produces" (this).
